            "<p><strong>Investigation 3</strong></p><p><strong>Using Unit Rates and Rate Tables</strong></p><p>A <strong>unit rate</strong> is a specific kind of ratio comparison in which one of the quantities being compared is 1 unit. We can use tables of equivalent ratios to help us find the unit rate.</p><p>When comparing how to share smoothie bars, Sofia records how many segments she and her sister would get for different sizes of bars. Sofia used equivalent relationships to make a table showing the amounts.</p>"
